We went in the Porch and Screens Passage and saw a painting of Sir Walter Raleigh, then we went into the Hall with the Great East Window which has 576 panes.The oak table is twenty feet long.In the Libary were two paintings by John Opie. Then we went to the stair-case, where on the window -sill is a Mandarin Duck and a figure in enamel of a cat.In the Drawing-Room is a picture with nine animals in it. The Court-Chamber is called the Court- Chamber because it over-looks the front court.The North Chamber has a tester bed in it.
{* * * * *}
